      "role": "user",
      "content": "Wait, if you're using salted hashes and tokenization, those are still reversible or linkable if someone has access to the mapping table or uses cross-referencing with other datasets. That's pseudonymization, not true anonymization. If a regulator finds out we're calling this 'true anonymization' when a simple cross-reference could de-identify the subjects, the compliance audit will fail and we'll be in serious legal trouble. Are you absolutely sure there is no way to reconstruct the original identities using the existing tokens and external data?",
